Just so you know, um the constructor is where we inject all of the dependencies that we need for this uh for this specific extension. And then I think the most important function is the activate function. So the activate function registered all registers, all the commands for visual studio code. So you can specify the. Read, config is more of a utility command. So you can see that the config is actually being read correctly depending on where it is. So for example, also like what are the default values that I did not provide that were added? So yeah, then the next command is obviously the start recording command, which is the core it still contains for my taste, a bit too much logic itself. But the basic idea is first get the focus information. So in which file is the current is the cursor currently. So where should we append the Vido reference? In our case? For example, this would have been at the top here. That's where my focus was when we started recording. If no window is open, we don't know where to edit, we don't record. But the main information like what is the database that actually stores it? It's just a bunch of Json files inside dot vic that contain all the information. So you could think of this as the database within each repository that is being generated and it references the files either on AWS or also within the repository. If you're using local saving strategy, then what is the text to a pen? So um basically that just generates this here that I show at the top which can later be detected by the extension. Then we insert this and then we start recording using the screen recorder, which is as specified in the other one an interface. But it was implemented once inside general screen recording RS screen recorder. So then there's a second command called stop recording which stops the recording. It then calls the post processing functionality. So there is a chain of post processing that can go on. First one is for example, uploading the file to S3 if that is specified if not. And we use the local strategy, move that file from the temp folder into the dot folder itself. Um and then do speech recognition and whatever else we might want to add, we can add into the post processing chain. Then we uh print that on the screen using the not, not and stop the indication of the recording. Meaning that at the bottom it should then be like it should stop the uploading thing and then once more refresh the decoration detection, meaning refresh the detection of Vido annotations within the file so that it immediately becomes yellow. Once uploaded this the bottom thing here, the all these things just called the commands that are specified here. So you will see that you can also do control shift P Vido start recording, stop recording here and it will do the same thing. Then there's a command for opening the video. So when we have a over a, let's look, for example here, if we hover over it, that's not a command. But if you click on this thing, you see command vido dot open video with a parameter. This will open the window for showing me the video. So that's this command. Then we have the win info command which is needed in order to detect the audio devices that should be used. Um This command is not being actually used. It's also for only then we have to select audio device which will force the reelect of audio device. So once you select an audio device, the audio device is being um saved as a user preference. So you don't always have to do it from scratch. But if you use the select audio device command, you can select the new one because then you don't need to go into the settings and change it manually. If you have switched something or you want to use a different device, then update decorations is what I just mentioned. It will look at the open files and check if it finds some video connotation that it could highlight with the yellow hover. And then um some other specific things that we don't need to go into. But then we register all these commands and that's it. So then there's one more thing which is register recalculation of highlighting, which is that we register this hover provider. So that um once we open a file, it will be checked. Is there any annotation? And if yes, make a hover effect on it or like make it yellow and then register the hover. That's basically this. So every time you open something it will check, does it find one or not? And then do the hover, you can deactivate it and um which just makes sure that any recording that is currently in progress is being stopped. So that's it. Quick introduction of the entry point VSC controller.
